            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think the problem is that darwin doesn't use a regex for the cores (`re = nil` in line 363) so it applies to _all_ cores. Of course it shouldn't touch cores from other programs; that should be fixed.\r\n\r\n(The _real_ issue is that darwin doesn't include the process _name_ in the core file...)",
