            "body": "> I think the problem is that darwin doesn't use a regex for the cores  (re = nil in line 363)\r\n\r\nOn macOS cores are named as /cores/corre.xxx where xxx is the PID, and filtering by regex is not possible, I think. Corefile name can be changed (for example to include the process name) by using 'sysctl' command but it requires root privilege.\r\n",
